  user_input {
    user_response: "# Velorah \342\200\224 Personal Website Style Brief\n\n## Stack\nReact + Vite + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui\n\n---\n\n## Fonts\nImport from Google Fonts: **Instrument Serif** (display) and **Inter** 400/500 (body).\n\n```css\n@import url(\'https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Instrument+Serif&family=Inter:wght@400;500&display=swap\');\n```\n\nCSS variables:\n```css\n--font-display: \'Instrument Serif\', serif;\n--font-body: \'Inter\', sans-serif;\n```\n\n- Body: `font-family: var(--font-body)`\n- All headings: `font-family: \'Instrument Serif\', serif` (inline or via utility class)\n\n---\n\n## Color Theme (dark, HSL CSS variables)\n\n```css\n--background: 201 100% 13%;        /* deep navy */\n--foreground: 0 0% 100%;           /* white */\n--muted-foreground: 240 4% 66%;    /* muted gray */\n--primary: 0 0% 100%;\n--primary-foreground: 0 0% 4%;\n--secondary: 0 0% 10%;\n--muted: 0 0% 10%;\n--accent: 0 0% 10%;\n--border: 0 0% 18%;\n--input: 0 0% 18%;\n```\n\n---\n\n## Liquid Glass Effect\n\nApply `.liquid-glass` to nav CTA and hero CTA buttons (and any frosted UI elements):\n\n```css\n.liquid-glass {\n  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.01);\n  background-blend-mode: luminosity;\n  backdrop-filter: blur(4px);\n  -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(4px);\n  border: none;\n  box-shadow: inset 0 1px 1px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);\n  position: relative;\n  overflow: hidden;\n}\n.liquid-glass::before {\n  content: \'\';\n  position: absolute;\n  inset: 0;\n  border-radius: inherit;\n  padding: 1.4px;\n  background: linear-gradient(\n    180deg,\n    rgba(255,255,255,0.45) 0%,\n    rgba(255,255,255,0.15) 20%,\n    rgba(255,255,255,0) 40%,\n    rgba(255,255,255,0) 60%,\n    rgba(255,255,255,0.15) 80%,\n    rgba(255,255,255,0.45) 100%\n  );\n  -webkit-mask: linear-gradient(#fff 0 0) content-box, linear-gradient(#fff 0 0);\n  -webkit-mask-composite: xor;\n  mask-composite: exclude;\n  pointer-events: none;\n}\n```\n\nUse `rounded-full` on pill buttons. Hover state: `hover:scale-[1.03]` with `transition-transform`.\n\n---\n\n## Animations\n\n```css\n@keyframes fade-rise {\n  from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(24px); }\n  to   { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }\n}\n.animate-fade-rise          { animation: fade-rise 0.8s ease-out 0s    both; }\n.animate-fade-rise-delay    { animation: fade-rise 0.8s ease-out 0.2s  both; }\n.animate-fade-rise-delay-2  { animation: fade-rise 0.8s ease-out 0.4s  both; }\n```\n\nApply staggered: H1 \342\206\222 `.animate-fade-rise`, subtext \342\206\222 `.animate-fade-rise-delay`, CTA \342\206\222 `.animate-fade-rise-delay-2`.\n\n---\n\n## Video Background\n\nFullscreen behind everything:\n\n```tsx\n<video\n  autoPlay loop muted playsInline\n  className=\"absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover z-0\"\n  src=\"https://d8j0ntlcm91z4.cloudfront.net/user_38xzZboKViGWJOttwIXH07lWA1P/hf_20260314_131748_f2ca2a28-fed7-44c8-b9a9-bd9acdd5ec31.mp4\"\n/>\n```\n\nNo overlays, gradients, or blobs on top. The video provides all visual depth.\n\n---\n\n## Navigation\n\n`relative z-10`, flex row, `justify-between`, `px-8 py-6`, `max-w-7xl mx-auto`\n\n- **Logo:** `\"Velorah\302\256\"` \342\200\224 \302\256 as `<sup className=\"text-xs\">`, `text-3xl tracking-tight`, Instrument Serif, `text-foreground`\n- **Nav links** (hidden mobile, `md:flex` gap-8): Home (active = `text-foreground`), Studio, About, Journal, Reach Us \342\200\224 `text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground transition-colors`\n- **CTA:** `\"Begin Journey\"` \342\200\224 `.liquid-glass rounded-full px-6 py-2.5 text-sm text-foreground hover:scale-[1.03]`\n\n---\n\n## Hero Section\n\n`relative z-10`, flex column, centered, `text-center`, `px-6 pt-32 pb-40`\n\n**H1:** `\"Where dreams rise through the silence.\"`\n- Classes: `text-5xl sm:text-7xl md:text-8xl leading-[0.95] tracking-[-2.46px] max-w-7xl font-normal animate-fade-rise`\n- Font: Instrument Serif\n- Wrap `\"dreams\"` and `\"through the silence.\"` in `<em className=\"not-italic text-muted-foreground\">` for tonal contrast\n\n**Subtext:**\n```\n\"We\'re designing tools for deep thinkers, bold creators, and quiet rebels.\nAmid the chaos, we build digital spaces for sharp focus and inspired work.\"\n```\n- Classes: `text-muted-foreground text-base sm:text-lg max-w-2xl mt-8 leading-relaxed animate-fade-rise-delay`\n\n**CTA:** `\"Begin Journey\"` \342\200\224 `.liquid-glass rounded-full px-14 py-5 text-base text-foreground mt-12 hover:scale-[1.03] cursor-pointer animate-fade-rise-delay-2`\n\n---\n\n## Design Principles\n\n- **No** decorative blobs, radial gradients, or overlays\n- **No** borders on the nav \342\200\224 just spacing and the liquid-glass CTA\n- Minimalist and cinematic: the video does the work, typography does the rest\n- All depth comes from the video background + glassmorphic elements\n- Generous negative space, tight leading on display text\n- Mobile: hide nav links, keep logo + CTA ,  use this as a reference and guide of styles to build my personal website about me, this is the information I want about me, and keep in mind that in the hero section I will have an animation of myself on it: \360\237\223\220 The Spatial Blueprint\nThe Right Hemisphere (The Visual Anchor)\n\nLocation: Spanning from the center line all the way to the right edge of the screen.\n\nContent: This is the dedicated, fixed space for your 3D spinning animation. It dominates the right side of the page, acting as the primary focal point exactly where the portrait sits in your example.\n\nThe Left Hemisphere (The Content Block)\n\nLocation: Anchored to the left-center of the screen, surrounded by clean empty space.\n\nContent: This is where your narrative lives. Your name, the text bringing together your engineering background and street preaching, and your action buttons sit here. As users scroll, this text area can transition to new sections while the 3D model on the right stays locked in place.\n\nThe Far-Left Spine (Fixed Vertical Navigation)\n\nLocation: A persistent, narrow vertical column pinned to the absolute left edge of the screen.\n\nContent: A top-left menu icon, followed by vertically stacked social and contact links (like your Instagram) spaced evenly down the side.\n\nThe Bottom-Left Zone (The Interactive Widget)\n\nLocation: Pinned near the bottom left corner, sitting below the main text block.\n\nContent: The inspiration image uses this space for a media player. For your site, this location is perfect for a compact functional module\342\200\224like a mini-player showcasing a project, a specific church event, or a quick highlight of your 140kg bench press.\n\nThe Far-Right Spine (Scroll Indicators)\n\nLocation: Pinned to the absolute right edge of the screen, floating over the animation.\n\nContent: Vertical numbers (01, 02, 03) that track the user\'s progress as they scroll through the different phases of your story. This is a brilliant concept. By leaning into a luxury, high-end aesthetic with a clean white background, the dynamic 3D animation of you will immediately grab attention. It acts as the perfect hook to show off your technical skills right away, proving to anyone from your Instagram or daily life that you can build top-tier digital experiences.\n\nHere is a proposed site structure, along with drafted text content and creative ideas to tie your multi-faceted life together into one cohesive, premium personal brand.\n\n---\n\n## \360\237\226\245\357\270\217 Website Architecture & Strategy\n\nTo balance the luxury aesthetic with your diverse background, the website should be a seamless, single-page scrolling experience. This keeps the user engaged with the animation while revealing different layers of your story.\n\n| Section | Purpose | Vibe |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| **1. Hero** | The Hook & Animation | Minimalist, premium, highly interactive. |\n| **2. The Builder** | Engineering & Tech | Sharp, professional, analytical. |\n| **3. The Foundation** | Faith & Community | Warm, authentic, grounded. |\n| **4. The Discipline** | Fitness & Drive | High-energy, intense, focused. |\n| **5. The Invitation** | Contact & CTA | Clean, welcoming, direct. |\n\n---\n\n## \342\234\215\357\270\217 Text Content & Copywriting Drafts\n\n### 1. The Hero Section\n\n*The visual here is the spinning, high-end 3D model of yourself on a pristine white background. As the user moves their mouse, the 3D model subtly follows the cursor.*\n\n* **Headline (Large, elegant typography):** Jo\303\243o Brito.\n* **Sub-headline:** Engineering systems. Building digital experiences. Sharing truth.\n* **Action Button:** Explore My Work\n\n### 2. The Builder (Engineering & Web Development)\n\n*This section highlights your professional and academic intellect.*\n\n* **Heading:** **Precision in Everything.**\n* **Body Text:** I am a 21-year-old Electrical Engineering student with a passion for how things connect\342\200\224from physical circuits to seamless digital interfaces. Bringing two years of corporate experience from Deloitte into my current projects, I blend analytical rigor with creative design. Whether orchestrating complex engineering solutions or designing luxury web experiences, my goal is always the same: build it beautifully, and build it to last.\n* **Feature Grid:**\n* **Electrical Engineering:** Academic projects and technical research.\n* **Digital Architecture:** High-end web development and interactive design.\n\n\n\n### 3. The Foundation (Faith, Church, & Teaching)\n\n*This section brings out your character, communication skills, and community involvement.*\n\n* **Heading:** **Driven by Purpose.**\n* **Body Text:** True power isn\'t just what we build; it is what we share. My life is deeply rooted in my faith. You will often find me on the streets of Lisbon, sharing the Gospel and connecting with people from all walks of life. I believe in the power of words and community, which is why I have also dedicated time to teaching Portuguese. Every interaction is an opportunity to uplift and inspire.\n* **Highlight:** A dedicated gallery or timeline of your church activities and street preaching moments.\n\n### 4. The Discipline (Fitness & Mindset)\n\n*This section shows your dedication and physical grit.*\n\n* **Heading:** **Discipline in the Iron.**\n* **Body Text:** The mind designs, but the body executes. Fitness is the crucible where I test my discipline. Hitting a 140kg bench press wasn\'t just a physical milestone; it was proof that consistency, patience, and absolute focus yield undeniable results. That same intensity fuels my studies, my faith, and my work.\n\n### 5. The Invitation (Call to Action)\n\n*The final pitch for those who want a website or just want to connect.*\n\n* **Heading:** **Let\'s Build Something Exceptional.**\n* **Body Text:** You are looking at my digital footprint\342\200\224a space I designed to reflect exactly who I am. If you are inspired by this interactive experience and want a premium, high-performance website that captures your own brand, or if you simply want to connect over engineering, faith, or fitness, my inbox is open.\n* **Action Button:** Start a Conversation *(Links to your Instagram DM or a clean contact form).*\n\n---\n\n## \360\237\222\241 Creative Ideas to Elevate the Site\n\n* **Scroll-Triggered Transitions:** Since the background is white, use bold, contrasting typography (like deep charcoal or elegant black) that fades or slides in as the user scrolls down.\n* **Easter Eggs:** Hide a small, clickable interactive element (like a tiny lightning bolt for electrical engineering or a barbell icon) that triggers a fun animation or a pop-up with a cool fact about you.\n* **Project Modals:** Instead of taking people to a new page, let your engineering and church projects open up in sleek, glass-morphism pop-ups over the white background.\n\nWhat kind of technologies or coding frameworks are you thinking of using to create this high-end 3D animation and layout? make a website\n "
    items {
      text: "# Velorah \342\200\224 Personal Website Style Brief\n\n## Stack\nReact + Vite + TypeScript + Tailwind CSS + shadcn/ui\n\n---\n\n## Fonts\nImport from Google Fonts: **Instrument Serif** (display) and **Inter** 400/500 (body).\n\n```css\n@import url(\'https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Instrument+Serif&family=Inter:wght@400;500&display=swap\');\n```\n\nCSS variables:\n```css\n--font-display: \'Instrument Serif\', serif;\n--font-body: \'Inter\', sans-serif;\n```\n\n- Body: `font-family: var(--font-body)`\n- All headings: `font-family: \'Instrument Serif\', serif` (inline or via utility class)\n\n---\n\n## Color Theme (dark, HSL CSS variables)\n\n```css\n--background: 201 100% 13%;        /* deep navy */\n--foreground: 0 0% 100%;           /* white */\n--muted-foreground: 240 4% 66%;    /* muted gray */\n--primary: 0 0% 100%;\n--primary-foreground: 0 0% 4%;\n--secondary: 0 0% 10%;\n--muted: 0 0% 10%;\n--accent: 0 0% 10%;\n--border: 0 0% 18%;\n--input: 0 0% 18%;\n```\n\n---\n\n## Liquid Glass Effect\n\nApply `.liquid-glass` to nav CTA and hero CTA buttons (and any frosted UI elements):\n\n```css\n.liquid-glass {\n  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.01);\n  background-blend-mode: luminosity;\n  backdrop-filter: blur(4px);\n  -webkit-backdrop-filter: blur(4px);\n  border: none;\n  box-shadow: inset 0 1px 1px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1);\n  position: relative;\n  overflow: hidden;\n}\n.liquid-glass::before {\n  content: \'\';\n  position: absolute;\n  inset: 0;\n  border-radius: inherit;\n  padding: 1.4px;\n  background: linear-gradient(\n    180deg,\n    rgba(255,255,255,0.45) 0%,\n    rgba(255,255,255,0.15) 20%,\n    rgba(255,255,255,0) 40%,\n    rgba(255,255,255,0) 60%,\n    rgba(255,255,255,0.15) 80%,\n    rgba(255,255,255,0.45) 100%\n  );\n  -webkit-mask: linear-gradient(#fff 0 0) content-box, linear-gradient(#fff 0 0);\n  -webkit-mask-composite: xor;\n  mask-composite: exclude;\n  pointer-events: none;\n}\n```\n\nUse `rounded-full` on pill buttons. Hover state: `hover:scale-[1.03]` with `transition-transform`.\n\n---\n\n## Animations\n\n```css\n@keyframes fade-rise {\n  from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(24px); }\n  to   { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }\n}\n.animate-fade-rise          { animation: fade-rise 0.8s ease-out 0s    both; }\n.animate-fade-rise-delay    { animation: fade-rise 0.8s ease-out 0.2s  both; }\n.animate-fade-rise-delay-2  { animation: fade-rise 0.8s ease-out 0.4s  both; }\n```\n\nApply staggered: H1 \342\206\222 `.animate-fade-rise`, subtext \342\206\222 `.animate-fade-rise-delay`, CTA \342\206\222 `.animate-fade-rise-delay-2`.\n\n---\n\n## Video Background\n\nFullscreen behind everything:\n\n```tsx\n<video\n  autoPlay loop muted playsInline\n  className=\"absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover z-0\"\n  src=\"https://d8j0ntlcm91z4.cloudfront.net/user_38xzZboKViGWJOttwIXH07lWA1P/hf_20260314_131748_f2ca2a28-fed7-44c8-b9a9-bd9acdd5ec31.mp4\"\n/>\n```\n\nNo overlays, gradients, or blobs on top. The video provides all visual depth.\n\n---\n\n## Navigation\n\n`relative z-10`, flex row, `justify-between`, `px-8 py-6`, `max-w-7xl mx-auto`\n\n- **Logo:** `\"Velorah\302\256\"` \342\200\224 \302\256 as `<sup className=\"text-xs\">`, `text-3xl tracking-tight`, Instrument Serif, `text-foreground`\n- **Nav links** (hidden mobile, `md:flex` gap-8): Home (active = `text-foreground`), Studio, About, Journal, Reach Us \342\200\224 `text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground transition-colors`\n- **CTA:** `\"Begin Journey\"` \342\200\224 `.liquid-glass rounded-full px-6 py-2.5 text-sm text-foreground hover:scale-[1.03]`\n\n---\n\n## Hero Section\n\n`relative z-10`, flex column, centered, `text-center`, `px-6 pt-32 pb-40`\n\n**H1:** `\"Where dreams rise through the silence.\"`\n- Classes: `text-5xl sm:text-7xl md:text-8xl leading-[0.95] tracking-[-2.46px] max-w-7xl font-normal animate-fade-rise`\n- Font: Instrument Serif\n- Wrap `\"dreams\"` and `\"through the silence.\"` in `<em className=\"not-italic text-muted-foreground\">` for tonal contrast\n\n**Subtext:**\n```\n\"We\'re designing tools for deep thinkers, bold creators, and quiet rebels.\nAmid the chaos, we build digital spaces for sharp focus and inspired work.\"\n```\n- Classes: `text-muted-foreground text-base sm:text-lg max-w-2xl mt-8 leading-relaxed animate-fade-rise-delay`\n\n**CTA:** `\"Begin Journey\"` \342\200\224 `.liquid-glass rounded-full px-14 py-5 text-base text-foreground mt-12 hover:scale-[1.03] cursor-pointer animate-fade-rise-delay-2`\n\n---\n\n## Design Principles\n\n- **No** decorative blobs, radial gradients, or overlays\n- **No** borders on the nav \342\200\224 just spacing and the liquid-glass CTA\n- Minimalist and cinematic: the video does the work, typography does the rest\n- All depth comes from the video background + glassmorphic elements\n- Generous negative space, tight leading on display text\n- Mobile: hide nav links, keep logo + CTA ,  use this as a reference and guide of styles to build my personal website about me, this is the information I want about me, and keep in mind that in the hero section I will have an animation of myself on it: \360\237\223\220 The Spatial Blueprint\nThe Right Hemisphere (The Visual Anchor)\n\nLocation: Spanning from the center line all the way to the right edge of the screen.\n\nContent: This is the dedicated, fixed space for your 3D spinning animation. It dominates the right side of the page, acting as the primary focal point exactly where the portrait sits in your example.\n\nThe Left Hemisphere (The Content Block)\n\nLocation: Anchored to the left-center of the screen, surrounded by clean empty space.\n\nContent: This is where your narrative lives. Your name, the text bringing together your engineering background and street preaching, and your action buttons sit here. As users scroll, this text area can transition to new sections while the 3D model on the right stays locked in place.\n\nThe Far-Left Spine (Fixed Vertical Navigation)\n\nLocation: A persistent, narrow vertical column pinned to the absolute left edge of the screen.\n\nContent: A top-left menu icon, followed by vertically stacked social and contact links (like your Instagram) spaced evenly down the side.\n\nThe Bottom-Left Zone (The Interactive Widget)\n\nLocation: Pinned near the bottom left corner, sitting below the main text block.\n\nContent: The inspiration image uses this space for a media player. For your site, this location is perfect for a compact functional module\342\200\224like a mini-player showcasing a project, a specific church event, or a quick highlight of your 140kg bench press.\n\nThe Far-Right Spine (Scroll Indicators)\n\nLocation: Pinned to the absolute right edge of the screen, floating over the animation.\n\nContent: Vertical numbers (01, 02, 03) that track the user\'s progress as they scroll through the different phases of your story. This is a brilliant concept. By leaning into a luxury, high-end aesthetic with a clean white background, the dynamic 3D animation of you will immediately grab attention. It acts as the perfect hook to show off your technical skills right away, proving to anyone from your Instagram or daily life that you can build top-tier digital experiences.\n\nHere is a proposed site structure, along with drafted text content and creative ideas to tie your multi-faceted life together into one cohesive, premium personal brand.\n\n---\n\n## \360\237\226\245\357\270\217 Website Architecture & Strategy\n\nTo balance the luxury aesthetic with your diverse background, the website should be a seamless, single-page scrolling experience. This keeps the user engaged with the animation while revealing different layers of your story.\n\n| Section | Purpose | Vibe |\n| --- | --- | --- |\n| **1. Hero** | The Hook & Animation | Minimalist, premium, highly interactive. |\n| **2. The Builder** | Engineering & Tech | Sharp, professional, analytical. |\n| **3. The Foundation** | Faith & Community | Warm, authentic, grounded. |\n| **4. The Discipline** | Fitness & Drive | High-energy, intense, focused. |\n| **5. The Invitation** | Contact & CTA | Clean, welcoming, direct. |\n\n---\n\n## \342\234\215\357\270\217 Text Content & Copywriting Drafts\n\n### 1. The Hero Section\n\n*The visual here is the spinning, high-end 3D model of yourself on a pristine white background. As the user moves their mouse, the 3D model subtly follows the cursor.*\n\n* **Headline (Large, elegant typography):** Jo\303\243o Brito.\n* **Sub-headline:** Engineering systems. Building digital experiences. Sharing truth.\n* **Action Button:** Explore My Work\n\n### 2. The Builder (Engineering & Web Development)\n\n*This section highlights your professional and academic intellect.*\n\n* **Heading:** **Precision in Everything.**\n* **Body Text:** I am a 21-year-old Electrical Engineering student with a passion for how things connect\342\200\224from physical circuits to seamless digital interfaces. Bringing two years of corporate experience from Deloitte into my current projects, I blend analytical rigor with creative design. Whether orchestrating complex engineering solutions or designing luxury web experiences, my goal is always the same: build it beautifully, and build it to last.\n* **Feature Grid:**\n* **Electrical Engineering:** Academic projects and technical research.\n* **Digital Architecture:** High-end web development and interactive design.\n\n\n\n### 3. The Foundation (Faith, Church, & Teaching)\n\n*This section brings out your character, communication skills, and community involvement.*\n\n* **Heading:** **Driven by Purpose.**\n* **Body Text:** True power isn\'t just what we build; it is what we share. My life is deeply rooted in my faith. You will often find me on the streets of Lisbon, sharing the Gospel and connecting with people from all walks of life. I believe in the power of words and community, which is why I have also dedicated time to teaching Portuguese. Every interaction is an opportunity to uplift and inspire.\n* **Highlight:** A dedicated gallery or timeline of your church activities and street preaching moments.\n\n### 4. The Discipline (Fitness & Mindset)\n\n*This section shows your dedication and physical grit.*\n\n* **Heading:** **Discipline in the Iron.**\n* **Body Text:** The mind designs, but the body executes. Fitness is the crucible where I test my discipline. Hitting a 140kg bench press wasn\'t just a physical milestone; it was proof that consistency, patience, and absolute focus yield undeniable results. That same intensity fuels my studies, my faith, and my work.\n\n### 5. The Invitation (Call to Action)\n\n*The final pitch for those who want a website or just want to connect.*\n\n* **Heading:** **Let\'s Build Something Exceptional.**\n* **Body Text:** You are looking at my digital footprint\342\200\224a space I designed to reflect exactly who I am. If you are inspired by this interactive experience and want a premium, high-performance website that captures your own brand, or if you simply want to connect over engineering, faith, or fitness, my inbox is open.\n* **Action Button:** Start a Conversation *(Links to your Instagram DM or a clean contact form).*\n\n---\n\n## \360\237\222\241 Creative Ideas to Elevate the Site\n\n* **Scroll-Triggered Transitions:** Since the background is white, use bold, contrasting typography (like deep charcoal or elegant black) that fades or slides in as the user scrolls down.\n* **Easter Eggs:** Hide a small, clickable interactive element (like a tiny lightning bolt for electrical engineering or a barbell icon) that triggers a fun animation or a pop-up with a cool fact about you.\n* **Project Modals:** Instead of taking people to a new page, let your engineering and church projects open up in sleek, glass-morphism pop-ups over the white background.\n\nWhat kind of technologies or coding frameworks are you thinking of using to create this high-end 3D animation and layout? make a website\n "
    }
  }
}
