    thinking: "**Assessing Scope and Skills**\n\nI\'m initially examining the user\'s brief, skills, and code to define the project\'s scope. My focus shifted to a skill relevance check. The preliminary assessment indicates that neither `firebase-integration` nor `gemini-api` is required based on the current instructions.\n\n\n**Analyzing Style Considerations**\n\nI\'m now diving deep into the style brief. There are several interesting items. I\'ve broken down the two parts, and I\'m focused on their interaction. The provided video background seems central, and the \"liquid glass\" effect is key to the design. I\'m noting the stack, fonts, and color theme, and how these elements integrate with the video and effects. I am making sure not to add any unnecessary features.\n\n\n**Defining Content & Purpose**\n\nI\'m now clarifying the website\'s core purpose. I\'ve pinpointed the user\'s name is Jo\303\243o Brito and that it\'s a personal website, aiming to showcase the user\'s personality. The hero section must include an animation of the user and it\'s essential to integrate the *Velorah* style brief elements, with emphasis on the specific video background URL provided and the overall deep navy color theme.\n\n\n**Mapping the Spatial Layout**\n\nI\'m now formulating the spatial layout based on \"The Spatial Blueprint\". My current focus is integrating the visual anchor, content block, far-left spine, and interactive widget into a cohesive structure. I\'m exploring various animation approaches, considering 3D CSS, Three.js, or other high-fidelity interactive elements for the central 3D animation. The left hemisphere will contain narrative and action buttons, transitioning into sections as users scroll. Fixed vertical navigation and an interactive widget in the bottom-left are also prioritized.\n\n\n**Integrating Visual Themes**\n\nI am now synthesizing the distinct visual directions. I\'m focusing on blending the clean, high-end aesthetic of the personal blueprint with the deep navy atmosphere of the Velorah style. I am now evaluating the viability of integrating a toggle feature between them. I\'m prioritizing the scroll indicators. I\'m now also considering displaying an event such as the 140kg bench-press.\n\n\n**Prioritizing Video & Visuals**\n\nI\'ve decided to prioritize the specified video background, as it directly addresses the \"no overlays\" requirement of the *Velorah* style. It seems that the video\'s abstract dark/liquid visuals can easily achieve the desired high-end, dark atmosphere. I\'m now actively brainstorming ways to incorporate this into an interactive, abstract particle model. I\'ve also reconsidered image generation, since I can create a custom, interactive visual representation using HTML5 Canvas instead.\n\n\n**Refining Interactive Assets**\n\nI\'m now zeroing in on an interactive canvas display, potentially a 3D structural head or biometric-style vector mesh, responding to cursor movement. This allows me to showcase coding prowess by crafting an engaging visual that responds directly to user interaction, offering an *insanely* impressive experience. The \"can build top-tier digital experiences\" line fits well, and I have all the skills to implement this. I\'m focusing on making this a standout feature.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 10
      nanos: 95891370
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
