  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Analyzing CSS Dependencies**\n\nI\'ve started examining the `index.css` file. My attention is currently on its dependencies. I\'ve noted the Google Fonts import, specifically the inclusion of `Instrument Serif` and `Inter` fonts. I\'m also beginning to identify the CSS variables declared within it.\n\n\n**Refining CSS Variable Analysis**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the CSS variables within the file, specifically their color definitions. The original thoughts were correct; these variables define the color theme. I\'ve realized that the alpha values are important. Additionally, I\'m noting the font families, `Instrument Serif` and `Inter`, and how they are assigned to CSS variables. I\'m noting the usage of these variables and attempting to identify any Tailwind-specific syntax.\n\n\n**Standardizing CSS Structure**\n\nI\'m now implementing standard CSS variables and classes, aligning with Tailwind CSS v4\'s `@theme` structure. I\'m focusing on defining core variables such as `font-sans`, `font-display`, `color-background`, and `color-foreground`. I\'ve added a `.liquid-glass` class and started defining keyframe animations, specifically `fade-rise`, which will be crucial for the UI.\n\n\n**Defining 3D Visuals**\n\nI\'m now contemplating how to create a premium, responsive 3D/2D particle avatar of Jo\303\243o Brito within a React component. My current thinking revolves around a code-only applet, avoiding complex dependencies. I\'m leaning toward an HTML5 Canvas for displaying a styled, interactive 3D wireframe face, geometric mesh grid, or a collection of rotating rings/spheres forming an abstract digital bust. This will be the visual anchor.\n\n\n**Designing Interactive Visuals**\n\nI\'m now deeply engrossed in designing an interactive vector canvas, aiming for a sleek, high-end aesthetic. I\'m imagining a floating particle grid, responding to mouse hover and scroll for dynamic interaction. Specifically, I\'m thinking of points on a face-like grid structure, projected to 2D using perspective projection for 3D illusion. The interactivity will stem from mouse physics to let users drag, spin, or rotate the 3D model, and let the wireframe consist of glowing interconnected dots forming a geometric pattern. I\'m focusing on crafting a custom component at `/src/components/InteractiveModel.tsx`. My focus extends to integrating this with the Hero section and \"The Builder\" section with the content requested by the user.\n\n\n**Structuring the Content**\n\nI\'m now focusing on the layout structure. The plan is a left-aligned narrative text section, changing with scroll. A fixed 3D model will be locked on the right. A pinned vertical navigation bar will be placed on the far left with menu icons, socials, and contact links. An interactive widget pinned at the bottom left will display a media player. I\'m aiming for an ultra-responsive design.\n\n\n**Implementing UI Features**\n\nI\'m now integrating a realistic-looking glassmorphic media player, allowing users to trigger audio and log targets. I\'m finalizing the far-right vertical numbers (01, 02, etc.) to track progress. I\'m structuring the layout with a left-aligned scrolling narrative and a fixed 3D model on the right. My goal is a truly responsive design.\n\n\n**Defining Layout Grids**\n\nI\'m now fully immersed in constructing the page layout. I\'ve sketched a grid with a left column for content spanning seven columns, and a fixed, interactive 3D model container taking up the right five columns. A fullscreen video background with a navy HSL background is now planned, as per the specifications, with no overlays. I\'ve been thinking about the absolute positioning of the video background and its opacity. I\'m focusing on responsiveness.\n\n\n**Defining Font Dependencies**\n\nI\'m now focusing on font files, and I will be declaring custom fonts in `src/index.css` using the Tailwind `@theme` directive, ensuring they are compiled correctly. I am setting up the directory structure and writing the `src/index.css` file. I\'m checking the correct syntax for `@theme` in Tailwind v4. I am currently considering a few new components such as `src/components/InteractiveModel.tsx`, `src/components/FarLeftSpine.tsx`, `src/components/RightSpine.tsx`, `src/components/InteractiveWidget.tsx`, `src/components/ContactModal.tsx`, and `src/types.ts`.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 18
      nanos: 579299492
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
