    thinking: "**Prioritizing Modular Design**\n\nI\'m now focusing on creating `/src/types.ts`. I want to centralize static data, types, and model configurations there. This aims to keep things modular and prevent excessively large files in `App.tsx`, which can cause issues with token limits.\n\n\n**Defining Data Structures**\n\nI\'m currently working on `/src/types.ts`. I\'m designing types and interfaces to represent all of the user\'s data: projects, activities, fitness logs, and personal sections. I\'m focusing on incorporating details about his bio, work, faith, and fitness into an interactive workspace. I\'m also planning an interactive widget for the bottom-left zone.\n\n\n**Designing Interactive Elements**\n\nI\'ve got a fantastic new concept! I\'m planning a multi-mode interactive player, which I\'ll call the \"Brito Ambient Player\" or \"Prism Suite.\" It\'ll feature an audio/focus deck with a waveform, a lifting tracker that simulates weight plates and calculates 1RM, and a project deck with code widget simulators. This is going to be incredibly engaging and is a perfect fit for the design.\n\n\n"
