  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Building Interactive Model**\n\nI\'ve decided to create `/src/components/InteractiveModel.tsx` for the right hemisphere. Now, I\'m focusing on crafting a premium, interactive, responsive, and personalized 3D spinning animation. The plan is to build a stunning Canvas-based 3D renderer within React to accomplish this goal.\n\n\n**Designing 3D Model**\n\nI\'m now diving deep into the 3D model design. The core concept revolves around a high-fidelity, futuristic geometric head. I\'m focusing on a particle mesh, visualized as dots and connecting lines, to represent the dual nature. This will involve an array of 3D points ($x, y, z$) forming the silhouette or a geometric polyhedron face. The plan is for dynamic rotation based on real-time and mouse coordinates, giving the illusion of the model \"looking\" at the cursor. Finally, the model should listen to scroll metrics.\n\n\n**Evolving Interactive Model**\n\nI\'m now focusing on dynamic visual transformations for the 3D model. The plan is to change its appearance based on the website section. For example, in the \"Builder\" section, it could shift to high-tech green/white circuits. I\'ll meticulously design vertices within the high-performance Canvas component. I will be working on a mathematical generator that outputs a grid representing facial structure or a stylized geometric bust with 100+ points and connecting edges.\n\n\n"
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 25
      nanos: 830613706
    }
