    thinking: "**Developing the Core Features**\n\nI\'ve successfully implemented structured types, along with an interactive 3D model. Navigation is streamlined with a left-side panel. A right-side tracker now displays the current phase. I\'ve also added a customizable local widget. This widget incorporates sound oscillator circuits, translator, and bench press trackers.\n\n\n**Integrating the Aesthetic**\n\nI\'m now integrating the visual design elements. This involves applying specific fonts (\"Instrument Serif\" and \"Inter\"), a dark HSL color theme, and a liquid glass effect to buttons. I\'ve also implemented staggered fade-rise animations for scrolling sections and a fullscreen background video. Finally, I\'m setting up the navigation with \"Velorah\302\256\" as the logo and links, which will target different sections within the application.\n\n\n**Refining Sectional Structure**\n\nI\'ve crafted elegant navigation by linking \"Reach Us\" to `#invitation`. I\'m now refining the spatial blueprint within `App.tsx`. The left hemisphere, the content block, is meticulously planned for narrative delivery with high-contrast elements. The right hemisphere is for the dominant 3D model. I\'m building a split-screen layout\342\200\224two-column desktop grid for the scrolling story content on the left, and a sticky, fixed frame for the interactive 3D model on the right. This layout aims for both desktop precision and mobile-friendly fluidity.\n\n\n"
