  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Initiating Portfolio Design**\n\nI\'m starting the full-portfolio implementation in `/src/App.tsx`. I plan to use state hooks for navigation, specifically an `activeSection` variable, which can be \"hero\", \"builder\", \"foundation\", \"discipline\", or \"invitation\". I\'m excited to get this project moving.\n\n\n**Implementing IntersectionObserver**\n\nI\'ve decided to employ an IntersectionObserver to dynamically track the currently visible section, replacing manual scroll handling, which I find far more reliable. I\'ll integrate state for `isContactOpen`, `isHubOpen`, and `forcePulseKey` for managing modal, sidebar explorer, and temporary 3D canvas pulses respectively. I am also working on CSS-based staggered animations with `animate-fade-rise`, `animate-fade-rise-delay`, and `animate-fade-rise-delay-2`. I have settled on a layout consisting of a header and a grid, with specific column spans.\n\n\n"
