    modified_response: "I have completed the luxury personal website for **Jo\303\243o Brito**, adhering closely to the **Velorah** cinematic design philosophy and your requested **Spatial Blueprint** layouts.\n\nHere is a proportional design and functional overview of the website:\n\n*   **Cinematic Video Atmosphere**: Embedded your custom looping video background behind a clean navy dark canvas. This provides all visual depth without unnecessary overlays, radial gradients, or margin clutter, letting the typography do the work.\n*   **The Left Hemisphere (Digital Content Narrative)**: \n    *   **The Builder (Chapter II)**: Outlines your Electrical Engineering academic focus, interactive analog hardware design, and two years of corporate consulting audits with Deloitte.\n    *   **The Foundation (Chapter III)**: Shares your absolute faith, detailing your street teaching and Gospel ministries in public squares from Chiado to Rossio, Lisbon.\n    *   **The Discipline (Chapter IV)**: Commemorates your daily training consistency and your physical metric of standard 140kg bench-press limits.\n*   **The Right Hemisphere (Vector Matrix Anchor)**: Features an interactive, high-fidelity HTML5 Canvas projection that simulates a rotating 3D biometric bust. This floating wireframe responds dynamically to your cursor coordinates and morphs its geometry and color spectrum (emerald, sky-blue, intensive amber) as you scroll through historical chapters.\n*   **Aesthetic Fixed Spines**:\n    *   **Far-Left Spine**: Houses a vertical navigation panel with active links to Instagram, LinkedIn, an inquiry connection form, and system status markers.\n    *   **Far-Right Spine**: Tracks scrolling progression with miniature active vertical numbers (01, 02, 03, 04, 05) representing each of your life\'s chapters.\n*   **The Bottom-Left Zone (Interactive Deck)**: Houses a sleek, glassmorphic widget allowing users to switch between three modes:\n    *   *Discipline*: A interactive rep counters and plate simulation showcasing the 140kg barbell.\n    *   *Foundation*: A conversational Portuguese translation switcher displaying core faith reflections.\n    *   *Analog Rig*: A Web Audio synthesizer simulating a 110Hz filter transient response with a live wave equalizer graph and volume slider controls.\n*   **Connective Modals**: Includes a sliding **Project & Mission Directory** for deeper academic exploration and a secure **Inquiry Transmission Form** to route potential business or ministry connections straight to you."
    thinking_duration {
      nanos: 557834368
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
